><dt><span class="term"><i><tt>win</tt></i></span></dt><dd>
						Identifier of GLUT window to destroy.
					</dd></dl></div></div><div class="refsect1" lang="en"><a name="glutDestroyWindow.3GLUT-description"/><h2>Description</h2><p>
			<tt>glutDestroyWindow</tt> destroys the window specified by win and the window's associated OpenGL context,
			logical colormap (if the window is color index), and overlay and related state (if an overlay has been established).
			Any subwindows of destroyed windows are also destroyed by <tt>glutDestroyWindow</tt>. If win was the
			current window, the current window becomes invalid (<a href="glutSetWindow.3GLUT.xml"><tt>glutGetWindow</tt></a> will return
			zero).
		</p></div><div class="refsect1" lang="en"><a name="glutDestroyWindow.3GLUT-see_also"/><h2>See Also</h2><p>
